President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key positions in his administration. 

1. Marvin Goodfriend of Pennsylvania is nominated to be a Member of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System for the remainder of a 14-year term expiring on January 31, 2030. Goodfriend is currently a professor of economics at Carnegie Mellon Universityâ€™s Tepper School of Business. He has extensive experience in the field, having worked for the Federal Reserve Bank of Richmond from 1978 to 2005.

2. Thomas E. Workman of New York is nominated to be a Member of the Financial Stability Oversight Council for a term of six years. Workman previously served as President & CEO of the Life Insurance Council of New York, Inc., representing numerous life insurers and other related firms. He also has a background in law, having practiced with Bricker & Eckler LLP in Columbus, Ohio.

3. Jeffrey DeWit of Arizona is nominated to be the Chief Financial Officer at the National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA). DeWit is currently the elected State Treasurer of Arizona and serves as Chairman of the Arizona State Board of Investments. He has a strong finance background, having worked as CEO of ECHOtrade and as a market maker on the exchange floor in financial futures contracts.

These nominations are subject to confirmation by the Senate.